## 6.5 Post-Incident & Recovery

Following an emergency or abnormal situation, the controller must ensure a safe and structured return to normal operations.

---

### 6.5.1 Immediate Post-Incident Actions

Once the situation is stabilised, the controller shall:

- Confirm the status of the aircraft  
- Ensure the runway is clear and safe  
- Maintain separation from other traffic  
- Continue to provide assistance as required  

The controller must not assume the situation is complete until confirmed.

---

### 6.5.2 Runway and Aerodrome Status

The controller shall:

- Confirm runway availability  
- Check for debris or obstructions  
- Coordinate inspection if required  
- Re-open the runway only when safe  

If emergency services are on the runway, it shall remain closed.

---

### 6.5.3 Traffic Recovery

The controller shall:

- Re-sequence arrivals as required  
- Resume departures in a controlled manner  
- Manage any backlog of traffic  
- Avoid creating additional conflicts  

Traffic flow must be restored gradually, not rushed.

---

### 6.5.4 Coordination After an Emergency

The controller shall coordinate with:

- Approach / Radar  
- Ground control  
- Adjacent sectors  
- Airport authorities  

Information to be shared includes:

- Aircraft status  
- Runway availability  
- Expected delays  
- Any operational restrictions  

---

### 6.5.5 Communication with Other Aircraft

The controller shall:

- Inform affected aircraft of delays  
- Provide updated sequencing instructions  
- Maintain clear and calm communications  

Example:

Due to earlier emergency traffic, expect delay, number three in sequence.

---

### 6.5.6 Controller Workload Management

After a high-stress event, the controller shall:

- Re-establish situational awareness  
- Reduce workload where possible  
- Request assistance if required  

Supervisors should monitor controller performance following an emergency.

---

### 6.5.7 Documentation and Reporting

The controller shall:

- Record the details of the event  
- Complete required incident reports  
- Notify supervisory staff  
- Participate in any required review  

---

### 6.5.8 Learning and Review

Post-event review should include:

- What occurred  
- Actions taken  
- Areas for improvement  
- Lessons learned  

This ensures continuous improvement in emergency handling.

